HEADWORD: paramedical
<hw>par`a*med"i*cal</hw>
<pr>(p⟦acr⟧r`⟦adot⟧*m⟦ecr⟧d"⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to those providing
medical care who are not physicians but serve in the capacity of
assisting physicians; nurses, physiotherapists, dieticians, Physical
Therapy instructors, and respiratory therapy technicians are examples of
<ex>paramedical</ex> personnel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the type of medical care
provided by paramedics or other <ex>paramedical</ex> personnel; <as>as,
<ex>paramedical</ex> treatment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parametritis</ent>⟦br⟧
